cafes.name: Koneko
cafes.address: 26 Clinton St, New York, NY 10002, USA

text.text: Amazing little experience where you get to place a brunch order, then play with a bunch of adoptable cats and kittens! After your time is up with the cats, you come back to the cafe and your food is hot and ready. Overall a very chill and fun experience, would totally recommend!

We stop here every time we visit NYC- the coffee is good, but we come for the cats. We're always happy to spend some money to support the adoption of the kitties. Make sure to make a reservation if you want to visit the cats!

Made a quick stop to Koneko Cafe. I ordered an iced strawberry matcha latte and it was better than what I expected, the balance between the sweetness of the strawberry and the matcha was perfect. To experience your coffee in the cattery a reservation is required in advance. Overall 4 star experience.

cafes.name: Meow Parlour
cafes.address: 43 Essex St, New York, NY 10002, USA

text.text:
We had so much fun at the Meow Parlour! The cats were so fun and the staff was very friendly. The coffee and pastries were delicious. There is a fun gift shop with so many cat themed goodies. If you’re looking for a fun and relaxing time hanging out with cats, this is the place for you.

The cat hangout area has a lot of seating as well as tables where you can do some work. You have to take your shoes off before entering the cat area. There is a place to hang coats and place shoes before going in. You can bring your drink and pastries in while you hang out with the cats. Can’t wait to go back, definitely recommend!

The floor was a little cold but apart from that it was nice. I would recommend wearing some thick socks and enjoy your time in there. The cats are very friendly and taken good care of. We were there at 4 pm and a few cars were asleep which is cool. I loved that the place didn’t smell and there was a restroom. The staff are nice and there is a little souvenir shop.

It was my first visit to Meow Parlour. Very cool place. I reserved a time online. There were probably 10 people in with me but it’s a large space/rooms so you have plenty of space to visit with all the cats.

There are many cat toys and cool cat tees and spaces for the cats to chill and nap.l the cats are great. Kittens and older cats. Amazing they all coexist. I love that they are lo available for adoption

There is a store in the front with cat toys, cute stickers, shirts, candles, and anything cat related. The team working the front and in the cat room were friendly and helpful.

cafes.name: COSMIC CAT COFFEE AND ESPRESSO
cafes.address: 170E E 2nd St, New York, NY 10009, USA

text.text:
Stumbled by this cozy coffee shop as I was walking around and stopped in as I saw it had great reviews. Cosmic Cat is a small warm cafe with minimal seating and very eclectic vibe inside with its decor. There was one barista making drinks who was super friendly.

I ordered just a cappuccino to try their espresso beans. My drink was good, the milk to coffee ratio felt balanced and went down smoothly. If I had one thing to pick apart, it would be that perhaps my milk was over steamed a bit as the drink came out extremely hot and burned my mouth, but after waiting a few minutes outside in the cold it was drinkable. Other than that seems like a solid spot for locals.
what a hidden gem!! Espresso is strong and delicious, not burnt or bitter at all. Dopest art on the wall too. Barista was so nice, definitely  a must go for good coffee
Cozy and delicious espresso. Not a lot of seating and no bathroom for customers as far as I could tell

cafes.name: Katz's Delicatessen
cafes.address: 205 E Houston St, New York, NY 10002, USA

text.text: Simply put, the best pastrami sandwich I have ever had.  I went Sunday morning which had no line whatsoever.   The pickles were pickling the bread was breading and the mustard lived up to the hype.  Pastrami was 28.95 a bit steepbut in my opinion well worth it.  The carvers were very friendly and the decor was a who’s who from Mike Tyson to Ben Stiller.  A true NYC dining experience that is unlike any other.  Highly recommended

Katz was an experience that I will always remember. The pastrami sandwich was really good and the shop is a part of over 130 years of history.
But there are few things to consider. First of all, the pastrami was quite fatty and after sometime, you might feel uneasy.
Secondly, their food waste is astonishing. The 31 dollar(with tax) is sometime more than enough for 2 people and if you are alone, you are doomed. People waste so much food that it makes you sad. There should be one option for around 20 dollars with half the meat and that should satisfy most of the population.
Nevertheless, if you are a company of two, order 1 sandwich and ask them for no cheese. The meat is fatty enough, you do not need cheese on top of that.

Another place in New York known for its movies and numerous publications. Interesting interior. Delicious pastrami sandwiches. There was a big queue at the weekend, so we went again and there was no queue on Tuesday. Recommend. #dookolaniczego

cafes.name: Black Cat LES
cafes.address: 172 Rivington St, New York, NY 10002, USA

text.text: I recently visited this place for the first time in years. It was really great to re-visit. It is warm and cozy, great coffee, small business. There was an open mic night for stand up. Really enjoyed it.
super cool vibes feels like a living room / old library. wifi password available if you purchase $5+. wine comes in a mason jar which is a nice touch. also there is a bathroom which is great

a lovely cafe with a dark ambiance, comfy couches and ample variety seating. WiFi, bathroom, great to get work done in or watch some stand up comedy (free every night @7pm!) It does fill up fast. The drinks are your standard cafe fare, reasonably priced, the barista can be a little cold but it matches the overall mood of the establishment!

As adorable as a Sleeping Cat! Roomy and full of wooden seats and comfy chairs, homemade pies and scones and their strawberry shortcake is so tasty and refreshing, topped with vanilla cream, strawberries, on their scones. Their iced latte was also so delicious! Would come back and work from here. Trying their pies next.

5 stars!!!

The Sleeping Cat is my new happy place! Everything is a 10!! The service is IMPECCABLE!! I HIGHLY recommend both the pecan pie and chicken hand pie. The crust is krypnoite!! Also, try the White Monkey tea. It’s a tasty green tea that’s inviting (even for a novice like myself) The Sleeping Cat is such a vibe🔥❤️🐱!!!

Such an incredible atmosphere and a unique idea, pies!!! Espresso was strong and service was good to.

Reasonable prices too!  Which is hard to come by.

I’m hoping they rotate the pies. I’m looking forward to maybe tasting a banana dulce? (Wink wink, owners if you’re reading this)

Had the best time with the kitties. They are everywhere and they love treats.
Getting there was super easy as well as the process to check in. Half an hour is enough time to go around give them some pets and maybe find one to play with for a bit if you are not planning on taking any home (tho I can assure you it’s super hard not to).
They also have 🐰
Wonderful experience!

Very cute spot and a lovely place to spend some time with their cats and kittens. Cats are up for adoption and there is an approval process. I would recommend reserving your tickets ahead of time if you can because it seems they’re strict on the entry and exit times. You have 30 minute sessions.

I wouldn’t call it a cafe since they don’t really make drinks but you can buy bottled water or coffee. Love the atmosphere and their cats are so sweet and playful.

Great cat cafe. They don’t really have a large selection of food or snacks so not much of a cafe but still a great experience. The cats are calm and like to be pet. Staff is super nice. Give them a try!

Unknown City.name: Cute Cat Cafe
Unknown City.address: 6669 Fresh Pond Rd, Ridgewood, NY 11385, USA

text.text:
June 2024: While looking for a new coffee place to go to while working on computer I decided on CCC.
Good reviews and lots of tables. Took a chance and glad I did. Will definitely be back! The one thing to note, they do not have AC. Their back and front doors were open and they have fans and today was warm but inside it was comfortable.
So if you must have AC, it won't be available here.
The women behind the counter today were super nice and brought my bagel to me. Nice touch.
Highly recommend this little coffee shop.

It’s a shame that i have overlooked this place for so long , but i finally gave it a chance and this cute cat cafe is now my go to for coffee. The ladies are always sweet and welcoming, great atmosphere. Their decor is one of my favorites to look at. From a board of customers’ napkin art to cat pictures. Their coffee is always delicious, it’s always fresh, and the best flavor 🩷

This coffee shop is awesome! It has great food, great service, and a friendly atmosphere. There is plenty of seating both inside and out and seems like an awesome place to do some work. The maple iced latte I had tasted really unique and I would recommend checking it out. If for nothing less than to try something new.

This is my favorite shop in the area. Super unpretentious and simple - exactly what i feel most people want early in the morning. Excellent coffee quality and atmosphere.

Hands down one of the best if not the best customer service in coffee I have ever experienced. The barista/ people that work there was so friendly and welcoming it made the drink much more enjoybale.

Just look at the leaf on the latte 6/5 stars

Just a nice little neighborhood spot to grab some great coffee with awesome service. The staff here is super nice. Their iPad was down this morning so they couldn't process payments. They gave us our coffee and pastries, and told us to “come back and pay tomorrow. I just wanna make sure you get your coffee.” So nice!
Free coffee when you buy a bag of beans! Very nice service
Wonderful ambience, great drinks, cute cats. Would heavily recommend to go out of your way

It’s a cute place only because of the claw machines, the lighting, and the cute ice cream. The service was very slow. It was just me and my husband inside the cafe. We only ordered 3 items - a mango slush, a watermelon slush, and a teddy bear mousse. It took about 15-20 minutes just to get our drinks. Add an additional 20 for the small bear mousse cake. All 3 items cost roughly $25. The little mousse cake, which could’ve been devoured in 2 bites by a man was $9. I’ve had better mango slush from other bubble tea places. The watermelon slush wasn’t bad. I believe they may have used real watermelon. In any case, I probably would not revisit, but it’s a great attraction spot for little ones. Be prepared to dish out money.
Such a cute little cafe for enjoying some boba and dessert. Super great lighting for fantastic looking photos. Claw machines is a nice touch. Hard to win prizes though but that’s expected.

Came here with my nephew + partner + family. It was a cute little spot with tea and claw games! The tea was pretty delicious and the claw games are very fun for those who like claw games (my partner) to enjoy.

Great little spot. The espresso was great and very full bodied.
Served on a tray with a sparkling water.

The atmosphere is very relaxed and the music chilled.
Perfect for a catch up conversation, reflection or book read.
There are small tables dotted everywhere.
There is a restroom/loo too.

The food variety is just simple breakfast pastries and sandwiches.
I had the melted cheese and egg sourdough toasted sandwich.

The area is very quirky with many restaurants around and easily accessible.
There is plenty of parking and a lot of side streets.

Overall, this was a great experience and super relaxed atmosphere.

the PERFECT cafe to work/study. it’s spacious, outlets at each table, tons of seating, and has AC. beautiful atmosphere and nicely decorated. good coffee too 🫶. will be my new go-to place.

my cappuccino with oat milk was $7.
Great place to enjoy pastries and coffee! The ham and gruyere croissant was delicious. Ideal spot for working, they have wifi and outlets available for use.
Best cat lounge we've been to! We had a very pleasant and calming experience visiting the lounge and playing with kittens. You also can feed them with treats. Will come back :)
Cute little space with adoptable cats you can visit for a very fair price. Met the founder and you could tell how much love and dedication is put into this place. Great vibes all around!
Good Home helped me foster and adopt my two cats and couldn’t be more supportive, responsive, and compassionate! I would highly recommend them as a foster or potential cat parent!!!

Amazing wonderful plave. Cats are so happy, clean and safe. We went back again for our birthdays ( my son and myself) and his girl Sophia.
Wonderful staff, great food n drinks. So enamored with the kitties, did not take too many pics, I was busy giving and getting love!! Next visit, picture time! 🩷🩵

Very pretty nice place to get a bite to eat and baby yourself with lovely playful kittens and cats. Croissant is so yummy. Owner is such a nice man god bless him. Staff is so friendly. Place is so clean and peaceful. Must go see.

great time w my 13yo and nieces. 9 & 8.  great lunch food, they brought us our sandwiches in the kitten room and we got to spend an hour with delightful balls of fur. the opportunity to foster or adopt were great - so we will foster some kittens. a wonderful lunch, great environment - so clean and spacious, an enjoyable time to explore kittens of so many different personalities.

The cats are adorable, and they all had good temperaments when we visited. There were a variety of personalities and energy levels, and you can tell the kitties are well cared for. Staff was very kind, and the drinks/desserts are worth ordering. Can't wait to go back!

My friend and I visited the Beans Cat Cafe in Beacon on January 4, 2025. We had such a great experience - we were able to book and pay for our reservation all online, they provided you with the rules and expectations so you knew in advance what to expect!

We arrived purchased our drinks and snacks and went right in to hang with the cats!! It was so FUN! I would totally go again!!

I went with my boyfriend 10/3/24 and it was awesome! Unfortunately we came when all the cats were sleepy but it was still a great experience getting to pet the cats and say hi. Before we left we got to say hi to Todd, Moose, Theodore, and I believe Tigresso. They were all so sweet and chill. Definitely recommend this place if you love cats and tea/coffee!!

I’ve been coming to Pawsitivitea for over 2 years now and have amazing experiences each time. If you are even the slightest cat person I would very much so recommend coming here as it is such a heartwarming environment. An hour with the cutest cats for only $10 and some change is an amazing deal. Pawsitivitea also offers the chance to adopt a wide variety of the cats that you will see upon visiting them, with an appropriate application process. Their tea and coffee beverages never disappoint as well as their fresh treats that they serve as well! Honestly such a great cafe. Overall every time I visit I have such a pleasant experience and would (and have) recommend this place to anyone who even remotely loves cats.

great coffee and awesome kitties. You can adopt but don't expect same day service. So be aware if you go with children as they may be sad that the kitty won't come home on the same day. They have an application process reffer to that for more details. They will check your references and vet doctor. so ensure your pet is up to date on shots. Over all 5 stars. =^..^=

This was my first time visiting, but it won't be my last!  Everyone was super nice, and the kitties were so adorable!  I was there for the holiday drag brunch, and it was such a great event!  I had been to drag shows before, but never a cat cafe, and my friend had been to cat cafes (Pawsitivitea specifically!) before, but never a drag show, so it was a really nice experience for us.  The cats were so fun, and it was also really nice to be in a space with other people who "get" cats.  Not to get too metaphysical about it, but I think cats demand a type of presence that isn't the norm in most other places in our culture.  It's nice to be around other people (and kitties!!) who really value being calm, respectful, and mindful of boundaries and subtle communication.  It's very peaceful - and the good food and drink certainly help too!  I really appreciated that everyone was so conscious of dietary restrictions too.  It was on the sign-up form, and they asked me again at the counter.  Everyone was really, really serious about not accidentally serving someone something that they can't or don't want to eat or drink.  I'm lactose intolerant and have definitely been dosed with full milk in some coffee places, so it's very noticeable to me when people are careful about it.  Thanks everyone, and I'll see you again soon!  Kiss the kitties for me!

New Haven.name: Mew Haven Cat Cafe
New Haven.address: 904 Whalley Ave, New Haven, CT 06515, USA

text.text: We visited Mew Heaven Cat Cafe on Sunday, and it was such a delightful experience! Booking our tickets ahead of time online was super easy and convenient. Once we arrived, we enjoyed some delicious coffee and tea while spending time with the adorable cats. The space is cozy, and the staff, especially Angela, the owner, was super friendly and welcoming. She really made our visit even more special. It’s the perfect place to relax and enjoy some time with furry friends. We had a great time and will definitely be back! Highly recommend for any cat lover!

This was such an amazing experience! The staff was so friendly. The gift shop prices were amazing! They also have a sheet on how each cat acts. A cat climbed up on my lap for around 30-40 minutes. It is such a beautiful and simple experience. I recommend that everyone goes here at least once. My only complaints are  that it's is only around 1 hour! Lol! I would spend all day here if I was able to! Also, It was around 30 minutes away! I wish there were so many more of these across the world!!!!! Overall, this was one of the best experiences of my life! If it is so relaxing and so enjoyable. I really hope to go back again soon!!!!!

This place is amazing! My granddaughter loved loved to pet the cats and she had a great time. I had a good relaxing time as well! I had cats as long as I can remember my self, so seeing all these babies today it was an amazing experience!! We will definitely visit you again.

New Paltz.name: Beans Cat Cafe
New Paltz.address: 11 Church St, New Paltz, NY 12561, USA

text.text: We were visiting family from Michigan, walking around the little downtown area of New Paltz, when I just happened to look down a side street and see "Cat Cafe". My daughter is a huge "cat lover" and I said, "oh my gosh, they have a cat cafe, do you want to go look in the window?" - we lasted all of 4 seconds before we were entering the front door, looking at spending some time with the sweet babies. My daughter and I each got a drink; we were told the ground rules (nothing surprising) and were advised to wash our hands upon entering. Immediately, I had the sweetest cats at my feet, rubbing my legs, looking for all the pets and love. My daughter had so much fun, and we both enjoyed our experience. if we didn't have a 10-hour drive and 2 cats at home, we would have applied to take one home. The kittens were so cute and playful. None of the cats were aggressive or ill tempered. My tiramisu cold brew was fantastic, and my daughter had a vanilla steamer. I found this place to be fairly priced and the cats seemed very well taken care of. The staff was friendly and told us all about the cats and where they came from and their stories. My ONLY issue with the cafe, as SOON as they opened the door to where all the cats were, the smell was awful. You can tell they really do try to mask or hide the smell and with that many cats, I'd imagine it's hard to do. But I couldn't even see litter boxes and the cat urine smell was fairly strong. All in all, if you love cats and want to enjoy 30 or so minutes of feline company and a tasty coffee, check out Beans! Took home a sweatshirt to remember my fun adventure with my girl.

Although we didn’t eat here. We went for my
daughter’s birthday to spend time with the cats. We did have coffee drink’s they were good. What impressed me the most was the place was very clean.The cats seemed well cared for. The litter box’s didn’t smell. The place is very well kept. We enjoyed our experience and we will definitely go back😻
Cats were so big and sweet! Loved playing and hanging out with them.  Great vibes, great tea, would hang again

Rahway.name: Rahway Kitty Hall
Rahway.address: 209 W Main St, Rahway, NJ 07065, USA

text.text: Not sure why a couple of recent reviews mentioned bad odor and scratchy cats. We were just there today and had a very pleasant experience - there were many sweet, playful kitties and no bad smells whatsoever. We haven't been to other cat cafes, and while those might be larger, this one was cozy and didn't feel cramped - there was enough space for both the visitors and the cats. All visitors are given disposable shoe covers to keep the place clean - great idea! Please note that the main door is locked, and visitors are let into the reception area in small groups to make sure the cats don't escape. There was a sign set up on the pavement, which we didn't notice, so another one on the door at the eye level would be very helpful. The volunteers were nice, gave us tips on which cats prefer being petted only on the head and answered all our questions. No food or drinks for sale, which is perfectly fine - the main purpose is to enjoy interacting with the adorable kitties and hopefully find a perfect match if you are looking to adopt.

You don’t buy food here, but you can reserve an hour online, sign a waiver, pay about $10 in person, and play with cats (toys and seats provided)! You are not supposed to pick the cats up. Parking is mostly street parking with meters/app. Second time coming with friends, and I love it! Friendly staff and fellow patrons!

I went here to pet the kittens and play with them. Upon entering, an almost unbearable smell. This place wasn't the cleanest. They offered a few toys and it was fun to play but most the cats were mean and we're biting and scratching. Please keep this place cleaner and let people know if the cats are friendly or not, I got scratched multiple times!!

Beautiful cat cafe. Very clean and all the cats were well cared for. The cafe was very nice with so much cat stuff and an array of other items. Just a beautiful place to visit. Highly recommend if you’re in the Albany area.

A really awesome place to pet cats and play with them. The owner is very friendly and there are a few snacks and drinks available. Cats are very friendly but please do follow the rules of the cafe. I would recommend booking a session online

Such a chill place. It was nice to sit back and relax with cats. They also have a couple of reptiles. The cats were all nice, and their rules were reasonable. There's limited food for humans, but a few drink options. It was enough for me, especially when the cays were the main stars.
